    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-07-26T18:31:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-07-26T18:31:00-05:00" n="508"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <head>508. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> of the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Jordan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d508fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 684A.85/7–2656. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_Niact1"
                        >Niact</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BDC1">Bergus</persName> and
                            <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">Burdett</persName>; cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_WFO1"
                            >Wilcox</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_AGV1">Allen</persName>;
                        and approved by <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">Burdett</persName> who signed
                        for <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>. Repeated priority to
                            <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, Tel Aviv, and London; pouched to
                        Paris, Moscow, and Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-07-26T19:31:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1956—7:31 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>88. For Chargé. You are requested seek immediate audience with King and make
                    following representations:</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> deeply concerned at continuing incidents
                    along <gloss target="#t_HKJ1">HKJ</gloss>–Israel armistice line. Without sincere
                    efforts by both parties situation can easily deteriorate further with
                    consequences no one can foretell. <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> not in
                    position assess blame for specific incidents. This is function of <gloss
                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>. We urge strongest cooperation with <gloss
                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss> in
                    carrying out of measures aimed at reducing present tensions.</p>
                <p>Frankness impels us communicate to King US concern at number of reports which
                    appear indicate lack well-disciplined efforts to maintain order along armistice
                    lines.</p>
                <p>Especially deplorable has been wounding of several <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1"
                        >UNTSO</gloss> observers while engaged in attempts pacify situation and
                    prevent further bloodshed. <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> observer personnel
                    should be afforded maximum protection. <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> urges
                        <gloss target="#t_HKJ1">HKJ</gloss> take all possible measures bring present
                    bloody cycle to immediate end. <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> making
                    similar representations to Israel Government.<note n="2" xml:id="d508fn2">See
                            <ref target="#d507">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> taking above initiative at request <gloss
                        target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> who curtailing leave Sweden flying New York
                    view present Palestine tension. <gloss target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> has
                    requested US, <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>, France, <gloss
                        target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> make strongest possible representations both
                    sides urgently.<note n="3" xml:id="d508fn3">See <ref target="#d506">Document
                            506</ref>.</note> End <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
